How many of you practice the 'Nose, Eyes, Ears' rule when meeting a dog for the first time?
Allowing a dog to experience our scent before we engage it in eye contact or speak to it is one way to establish trust early on.
Dogs begin with the nose, then the eyes, and lastly the ears.
I remind dog owners that dogs see the world differently from the way we do. We communicate using our ears first, then our eyes, then nose.
You've probably heard me say "Nose, Eyes, Ears... In that Order." Yes?
